k up at him. The man gestures with open hands, as if addressing both sides of the crowd or moderating a dispute.\n\nHe steps down beside the bus and continues speaking among the group. A muddy adult man in a dark vest and knit cap stands near him, smiling. The suited man holds a small white mobile phone in one hand, using it almost like a prop while he talks. Behind him, the bus door and steps are open, and the red and grey side of the bus fills the background. Several muddy children and adults watch, some smiling, some looking curious.\n\nA young Black woman or older teenager in a white knit headband and a light, mud-streaked jacket smiles at him from the crowd. Her face and clothes are marked with dark smears of mud. Behind her, a man in an orange knit cap, also muddy, grins. A younger woman or girl in a pink knit hat appears nearby, smiling as well. The group’s expressions suggest they are amused and engaged rather than angry, despite the messy, competitive setup.\n\nThe suited man stands beside the bus with the small white phone held out in his right hand. Around him are muddy kids and adults, including a child in a grey hoodie and knit cap and others in pastel winter hats. He spreads his hands slightly while speaking, then turns toward the muddy young woman in the white headband. She smiles back, standing with a relaxed posture. The phone remains visible in his hand as a clear visual focus.\n\nA younger Black girl or teenager in a white crocheted knit cap and a cream-colored hoodie, both heavily stained with mud, becomes the focus. Mud streaks mark her cheeks and the front of her hoodie. She stands among adults and children, looking toward the suited man. At first she smiles politely, then her expression becomes animated. She opens her mouth wide as if making an emphatic point, glances upward and to the side, and gestures with a gloved or muddy hand. An older woman in a pink hoodie and knit cap stands to her left, smiling, while a tall man in a dark green jacket stands behind her. The girl’s face shifts from serious emphasis to a bright laugh, and the people around her smile along.\n\nThe suited man turns back toward the group by the bus, holding the white mobile phone up near his face as he continues. The muddy young woman in the white headband stands to his left, and a bald man in a dark jacket is close on his right. The bus’s red and grey side fills the background, and the black Sprint sign is partly visible above them. He raises the phone higher, presenting it to the people gathered around him.\n\nThe crowd then stands in a wider group facing the side of the Sprint bus. The large black panel on the bus clearly shows the white word “Sprint” with the red diamond logo. The suited man stands near the center of the group, still holding the phone up. The muddy adults and children form a ring around him, looking toward the bus display. The black display on the side of the bus changes from the large Sprint logo to smaller white text, but the lettering is too small and blurred to read clearly here. The group remains gathered in the muddy field, focused on the bus and the man’s presentation.\n\nLater, the suited man stands away from the bus with two muddy young women or girls in the park. One, taller, is on the left, wearing a white headband and a light jacket or hoodie streaked all over with mud; her face is also smeared. The younger one in the middle wears the white crocheted cap and cream hoodie, also heavily muddy. The suited man, still clean in his dark suit and tie, holds the small white mobile phone out toward the younger girl. She smiles broadly and reaches for it with muddy hands.\n\nThe younger girl takes or steadies the phone and looks down at it, grinning. The taller young woman beside her laughs and watches. In the background, other muddy people walk across the wet field, and park items such as coolers or bags sit near the path. The suited man withdraws his hand and stands upright, watching the girls with a composed expression.\n\nThe younger girl holds the phone up between herself and the suited man, still smiling. The taller young woman gestures with muddy hands, laughing, and the younger girl looks delighted. Their clothing and hands are so muddy that the clean white phone contrasts sharply against the dark smears. As the moment continues, both girls look down toward the phone and their muddy palms, amused by the mess. The suited man remains facing them, his clean black suit standing out against the mud-covered field and the playful, dirty crowd behind them.",
